com.betfair.cougar.transport.impl.protocol.http

Class AbstractHttpCommandProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.betfair.cougar.transport.impl.AbstractCommandProcessor<HttpCommand>
      • com.betfair.cougar.transport.impl.protocol.http.AbstractHttpCommandProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GateListener, HttpCommandProcessor, TransportCommandProcessor<HttpCommand>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractTerminateableHttpCommandProcessor, JsonRpcTransportCommandProcessor, ServiceNotFoundHttpCommandProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractHttpCommandProcessor
extends AbstractCommandProcessor<HttpCommand>
implements HttpCommandProcessor, GateListener
    Provides common functionality for Http CommandProcessors, mainly around resolving the ExecutionContext from an HttpCommand, and registration as a GateListener.

      • resolveContextForErrorHandling

        protected ExecutionContextWithTokens resolveContextForErrorHandling(ExecutionContextWithTokens ctx,
                                                        HttpCommand command)
        Resolves an HttpCommand to an ExecutionContext for the error logging scenario. This will never throw an exception although it might return null. The process is:
      • If a non null context is passed,us it
      • Otherwise try and resolve a context from the commmand
      • If that fail, return null
Parameters:
ctx - the previously resolved context
command - contains the HttpServletRequest from which the contextual information is derived
Returns:
the ExecutionContext, populated with information from the HttpCommend

    public void writeIdentity(List<IdentityToken> tokens,
                 AbstractHttpCommandProcessor.IdentityTokenIOAdapter ioAdapter)
    Rewrites the caller's credentials back into the HTTP response. The main use case for this is rewriting SSO tokens, which may change and the client needs to know the new value.
